@vrothberg  you are mvp man! can i ask if there is more detailed docs than 
https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/_static/api.html

it's literally just endpoints, and im shooting from the hip looking at Go code...

Glad it's working, @avnav0.

You are using /containers/create which is the Docker compatible endpoint documented [here](https://docs.docker.com/engine/api/v1.43/#tag/Container/operation/ContainerCreate). [/libpod/containers/create](https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/_static/api.html#tag/containers/operation/ContainerCreateLibpod) does not seem to be well documented; at least I cannot find a reference to the JSON.

@mheon, am I looking at the wrong place?

@mheon hey thanks for this (we commented at the same time)

taking a look:

```
Entrypoint []string `json:"entrypoint,omitempty"`
	// Command is the container's command.
	// If not given and Image is specified, this will be populated by the
	// image's configuration.
	// Optional.
Command []string `json:"command,omitempty"`
	// EnvHost indicates that the host environment should be added to container
	// Optional.
```
is there a way to see where the code goes - for example how `Command` translates to `cmd`
